{
  "stem": "304.4",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then I would pay with my life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So nobody tried to escape.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But escape itself would have been easy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It just wasn't easy because you have to go somewhere.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[DRINKS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The end of the war-- we knew that the war is going to end.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We always heard news.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If they were good, we believed them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If they were not good, we called them German propaganda.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Of course, we wanted always to believe that the war will be-- go to an end, and we will survive.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in April, we knew already that the Allies are closing in.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we didn't  know if it would last a month, two, five, six.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know how, how long.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So one day, we were ready to go to work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were standing outside, the day shift, 6 o'clock in the morning-- no, before 6:00.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- but we didn't go to work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They let us stand there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the night shift who came back, they didn't let them to go inside the barracks.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were standing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they said, we are going away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And somehow-- we had blankets in this camp already.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We run back to the barracks and grabbed our blanket.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything else was on us what we had, the, the dress and the coat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then we started on a march.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were marching-- in the literature of the Holocaust, it's called a 'death march,' because a lot of people lost their lives on those marches the last weeks of the war.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or even not the last weeks-- I think my brother lost his life because he was on a march in February.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In February in Europe, to march without shoes in the cold, a lot of people lost their lives.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
